  <summary>4/22/2003--Public Law.
(This measure has not been amended since being passed in the House on February 26, 2003. The summary of that version is repeated here.)Designates the Guam South Elementary/Middle School of the Department of Defense Domestic Dependents Elementary and Secondary Schools System in Apra Heights, Guam, as the "Commander William C. McCool Elementary/Middle School," in honor of William C. McCool, who was a commander in the U.S. Navy and pilot of the Space Shuttle Columbia when it was tragically lost on February 1, 2003.</summary>
